cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.SC 

This paper is about deep learning algorithms for distributed, heterogeneous data. The primary focus is on stochastic gradient descent (SGD) algorithms, which are commonly used in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary category for papers on deep learning. The paper also discusses distributed computing and data management, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with data processing and analysis, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SC (Scientific Computing). Finally, the paper discusses neural networks and optimization, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
